@node file_list "FullTime File List"
FullTime File List
------------------

FullTime        The main program.
Customise       If you register the program, you will need to run this
                program to input the registration key.
Data            Directory containing all the data on the leagues and teams
Fixtures        Directory where all the fixture files are stored

There are also a few other files, in the main directory without Icons. If you copy the program to a different directory, make sure you copy these files too.
@endnode
                              
@node using "Using FullTime"
Using Full Time
---------------
    When the program is run, you are presented with a menu with the
following options:

    @{" 1 " link update}  Update Results 
    @{" 2 " link enter}  Enter Fixtures
    @{" 3 " link load}  Load Fixtures off Disk
    @{" 4 " link forcast}  Forecast Results
    @{" 5 " link statistics}  Team Statistics
    @{" 6 " link changedivinfo}  Change Division Information
    @{" 7 " link teamname}  Change Team Name
    @{" 8 " link newseason}  Start New Season (Promote/Relegate/Add Teams)
    @{" 9 " link end}  End Program
@endnode

@node history "FullTime History"
@{B}V1.22   Released 11/11/1998@{UB}
* Program will now open and run properly on a standard high-resolution
  workbench screen. Because of a bug, the previous version needed hires
  interlaced, or a VGA screen to work.
@{B}V1.21   Released 17/10/1998@{UB}
* The forcasting routines have been tweaked to hopefully improve the
  success rate
@{B}V1.20   Released 12/09/1998@{UB}
* An option has been added allowing team names to be changed.
* The Team Statistics screen has been redesigned. A bar graph shows each
  team's home and away form.
* Various bug-fixes and enhancements to the program have been made
@{B}V1.15   Released 12/07/1998@{ub}
* 'New Team' Confirmation can now be turned off (WB 2.0 + only) speeding up
  entry of new teams in 'Start New Season (Promote/Relegate/Add Teams)

@{B}V1.10   Released 19/04/1998@{ub}
* Now Supports up to 12 divisions.
* The unregistered version of the program will now only display the 
  results of the first two divisions (English Premiership and Division 1)
* The program will now not allow you to accidentally enter the results of     fixtures more than once.
* Corrections to 'Program Performance' display made.
* Other minor bug fixes made.

@{b}V1.01@{ub}
* Problem in Fixture Cancellation routine corrected.
* Incorrect Program Performance figures corrected. 

@{b}V1.00@{ub}
* First public release
@endnode
@node update
Update Results
--------------
Use this option to update the database with the results of the matches you predicted. Just enter the score against each team name. Click 'OK' when all the scores for the current division have been entered, the fixtures for the next division will then be displayed. If you make a mistake, you can use the mouse to click on a team and re-enter a score. If a result is not known, just press enter to skip the fixture. It can be entered later.
@endnode
@node enter
Enter Fixtures
--------------
Before you can make any predictions you must enter the fixtures. You will be presented with the list of teams in the current division. Repeatedly clicking on first the home team, then the away team, enter your fixtures. If you make a mistake, click on the fixture, and you will be given the option to cancel the fixture, putting the teams back into the team list.

When you have entered all the fixtures for that division, use the pull down menu to select a different division. And when all the fixtures have been entered, click on 'All Done'.
@endnode
@node load
Load Fixtures off Disk
----------------------
Use this option to load into memory fixtures which you've previously entered and now wish to forecast or update the results
@endnode
@node forcast
Forecast Results
---------------
Once you've entered some fixtures, or loaded them in off disk, you can then forecast the results. You are given the option to see the results on screen, printed, or both. The program will make a prediction for every fixture you entered, but only the results marked with a '*' or 'D' should be considered as reliable.
@endnode
@node statistics
Team Statistics
---------------
This option allows you to view the statistics of a team. Use the pull down menu to change division.
@endnode
@node changedivinfo
Change Division Information
---------------------------
This option allows you to change the division names, and tell the program where teams should be promoted or relegated to. If a division does not have Promotion or relegation, put a '0' in the relevant field.
@endnode
@node newseason

@node teamname
Change Team Name
----------------
Team names can be changed using this option. 
Care should be taken when using this option mid-season as after a team name is changed, the teams in that division are re-sorted alphabetically. You will not be able to load and use any previously saved fixture files in FullTime if the teams are in a different order after being sorted.
@endnode
Start New Season (Promote/Relegate/Add Teams)
---------------------------------------------
Use this option at the end of a season. Teams can be promoted, relegated, or a new team entered into a division. This option must only be used at the end of a season as it resets all the games played for each team to zero.

FullTime's accuracy increases as more data is input. It does not carry over all the data from the previous season, so for the first few weeks, it's predictions will not be so accurate. It really needs at least 4 weeks worth of data, before it can be used as a prediction system.
@endnode
@node end
End Program
-----------
You should be able to work this option out yourself.
@endnode

@node otherleagues
Using The Program With Other Leagues/divisions
----------------------------------------------

   THESE PROCEDURE CAN ONLY BE DONE BEFORE THE FOOTBALL SEASON STARTS!

Full time is set up to predict the results of the English and Scottish football leagues. It can be used with any league as long as each division has 30 or less teams, and there are 12 or less divisions.


@{b}Adding a new division@{ub}

1  From the Main Menu, choose option 6 - Change Division Information.
   Click in the next available slot and enter the new division name.
   Enter the promotion and relegation paths in the relevant boxes.
   
2. From the main menu choose option 7 - Start New Season.
   Step through all the divisions, promoting and relegating teams as you
   go.
   When you get to the new division, enter all the teams one by one in the
   'New Team' gadget. You do not need to enter them in alphabetical order,
   the program will handle that.
 
@{b}Replacing one division with another@{ub}

1  From the Main Menu, choose option 6 - Change Division Information.
   Enter '0' for the relegation path of the division you want to delete.
   Replace the current division name with the new one.

2  From the main menu choose option 7 - Start New Season.
   Step through all the divisions, promoting and relegating teams as you
   go.
   When you get to the division you want to delete, select all the teams
   and press 'Relegate'.
   Then enter all the new team names one by one in the 'New Team' gadget
   You do not need to enter them in alphabetical order.

3  Go back to menu option 6 and replace change the relegation path to the
   path for the new division.
  

@{b}If you want to replace all the current divisions with divisions
from a different league eg Australian League@{ub}
   
1  If you wish to set up a different league, first delete all the files in
   the Data directory (or rename the directory and make a new 'Data'
   Directory).

2  Next, run the program and choose option 'Change Division Information',
   and input the names of the divisions, and promotion and relegation
   routes.

3  Choose 'Start New Season' and then enter the team names for each
   division. You do not need to enter the teams in alphabetical order, the
   program will do that once you have finished entering teams.

You can now start using FullTime with your chosen league. The accuracy rate
will increase as you input more data. It's best to allow at least 4 weeks
worth of data to build up before you start using the program to forecast
results.
@endnode
